Amazon VPC - Introduction to Amazon Virtual Private Cloud
Last Updated : 14 Jan, 2026

Amazon Virtual Private Cloud (VPC) is the fundamental networking layer for your cloud infrastructure. It allows you to provision a logically isolated section of the AWS Cloud where you can launch AWS resources in a virtual network that you define.

Think of a VPC as your own private data center in the cloud. You have complete control over your virtual networking environment, including selection of your IP address range, creation of subnets, and configuration of route tables and network gateways.
